### Mobile Testing - HTTP Endpoints (Port 8080)
### Use these endpoints for mobile app testing to avoid SSL certificate issues

### Create a new User (HTTP)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/cmd/user HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
accept: application/json
X-API-Version: 1

{
  "username": "mobiletester123",
  "email": "mobile.tester@example.com",
  "password": "testPassword123",
  "firstName": "Mobile",
  "lastName": "Tester",
  "birthDate": "1995-03-10"
}


### Create another User (HTTP)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/cmd/user HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
accept: application/json
X-API-Version: 1

{
  "username": "appuser456",
  "email": "app.user@example.com",
  "password": "appPassword456",
  "firstName": "App",
  "lastName": "User",
  "birthDate": "1988-07-20"
}


### Get User by Entity Key (HTTP)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/qry/user?entityKey=3ctn0Jm&size=lg HTTP/1.1
accept: application/json
X-API-Version: 1


### Check if username exists (HTTP)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/qry/user/check-username?username=mobiletester123 HTTP/1.1
accept: application/json
X-API-Version: 1


### Check if username exists - non-existing (HTTP)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/qry/user/check-username?username=nonexistentuser HTTP/1.1
accept: application/json
X-API-Version: 1


### Check if email exists (HTTP)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/qry/user/check-email?email=mobile.tester@example.com HTTP/1.1
accept: application/json
X-API-Version: 1


### Check if email exists - non-existing (HTTP)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/qry/user/check-email?email=nonexistent@example.com HTTP/1.1
accept: application/json
X-API-Version: 1

### Upload a profile picture for a registered user (HTTP)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/cmd/user/3ctn0Jm/picture
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
X-API-Version: 1

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="image"; filename="testImage.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< C:\Users\midor\Pictures\testImage.jpg
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

